body_html:
@aashish-kumar : It seems you're running fully_connected_feed.py from the HEAD of the git repository, which is incompatible with the release version (in particular because of change 8532897)

Many examples are installed with the release, so you would find some files in:
/home/aashishk/anaconda2/envs/tensorflow/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist

However, since fully_connected_feed.py is not used in the website tutorials, we don't include it with the release. That said, you can find the versions that work with the release in the release branches on git.

  • For 0.10
  • For 0.11

Hope that explains the situation and helps you get out of it :)
I'm going to close this issue since I believe it is resolved, but if not, feel free to reopen it.

Thanks!

body:
@aashish-kumar : It seems you're running `fully_connected_feed.py` from the HEAD of the git repository, which is incompatible with the release version (in particular because of change https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/commit/8532897352ada1d8ecd3ca1dd17aaa869a42d4b8)

Many examples are installed with the release, so you would find some files in:
`/home/aashishk/anaconda2/envs/tensorflow/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist`

However, since `fully_connected_feed.py` is not used in the website tutorials, we don't include it with the release. That said, you can find the versions that work with the release in the release branches on git.
- [For 0.10](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/r0.10/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist)
- [For 0.11](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/r0.11/tensorflow/examples/tutorials/mnist)

Hope that explains the situation and helps you get out of it :)
I'm going to close this issue since I believe it is resolved, but if not, feel free to reopen it.

Thanks!
